<br>
- NPC's that do something else than stand there. Have them walk around, chat amongst each other, that sort of thing...there are too few NPC's in the game that do this, imho.<br>
<br>
- NPC's of different ages..anyone ever seen an old person in EQ? <br>
<br>
- Keyrings.<br>
<br>
- Birds flying in the sky (flying monsters too - imagine Gorenaire flying over the Dreadlands instead of stomping through the tundra).<br>
<br>
- Constellations of stars that I can navigate by.<br>
<br>
- A dynamic weather system, including fog &amp; mist.<br>
<br>
- More dynamic sound/music. For examples, take a look at the sound engine for Thief/Thief 2. The sound makes you feel like you're really there.  Especially for cities, they should feel like they are teeming with life, not sterile, manufactured environments.<br>
<br>
- Housing (additional zones off of the major cities could be used as space for this).  Various styles of housing dependant on culture.<br>
<br>
- A working archery system.  I want to know how Wood Elves are supposed to have fought Orc armies from the trees if they were &quot;too far above/below&quot; their targets...<br>
<br>
- Revamps for the city zones. Make them feel like a city instead of a small town.  If it was at all possible, form all the existing multi-zone cities into one zonefile (for example, combine North &amp; South Qeynos, or the three parts of Neriak).  <br>
<br>
- More rooftops that you can run over - implement Norrath's Rogue's Highway, complete with ledges, chimneys into buildings, washing lines, flagpoles, etc)<br>
<br>
- Surrender emotes for duelling.  I don't want to see someone just fall over in front of me, I want to see them grovel on their knees in the dust for mercy! /roar<br>
<br>
- a variety of death animations, based on the way you died. When someone dies from dragonfire, I want them to run round like human torches for a bit, ala &quot;Syndicate&quot;.<br>
<br>
- Random sitting animations, so we don't look like some sort of bizarre cult waiting outside of banks and such =)<br>
<br>
- Activate the firepot network between cities...put the batteries back into Miragul's Highway.  That should help the wizards/druids getting begging tells every minute.<br>
<br>
- Affordable horses.  Keep the *really* fast ones for status symbols, if you have to.<br>
<br>
- Dual-classing (Ranger-rogue, here)<br>
<br>
- More PvP zones like the Arena, but with mobs, to make things interesting.<br>
<br>
- Mobs called &quot;The Vision&quot; and &quot;Verant&quot; - they'd be camped 24/7...&quot;You have killed The Vision!&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
- a new spell effects engine. Following Luclin it would be a good addition, something in line to match the new models.<br>
<br>
That's all I can think of offhand...will come back with more later. =)<br>
<br>
Edit #1: Told you I'd be back later <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Natural disasters. Earthquakes, volcanic eruptions (especially in Skyfire and Lavastorm, and maybe in Steamfonts?), tidal waves or floods.  Give the community something to band together against on a large scale, short of a massive invading force<br>
<br>
- more zone updates, but not just in level of creatures or changes to loot table. I'd like to see the actual scenery change. Have Mayong Mistmoore commanding a legion of slaves to build more towers or dig catacombs beneath his castle, for instance.  That would give us a changing environment to explore as well as new creatures to fight and items to gain.  Have more zones appear off of existing zones (for instance, the &quot;Catacombs of Mistmoore&quot; as mentioned above).<br>
<br>
- Crew on the boats.  The Ship's Captain (the ones that call out when the boats enter zones) and a barkeep at least!<br>
<br>
- implementation of all the Old World zones that have been missed so far (take a look at the EQ world map, there is a lot more to Norrath than has been explored to date).<br>
<br>
More soon...<br>
